keywords.previousInsuranceProviderOtherProviderMo: You will have to contact your old insurer and terminate your insurance yourself if you choose to become a member with us later.

passages.name: emailAddressVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  OK! Enter you email address below to proceed to your price quote
</Message>

<TextAction placeholder="your.email@here.now"
            mask="Email"
            key="email"
            next="[[Nästa->Offer]]"
>
</TextAction>

passages.name: personalNumberApartment
passages.text:
<Message>
  OK! All we need now is your swedish personal number so that we can automatically fetch the rest of the information needed to create your offer
</Message>

<Redirect when="householdSize > 6"
          to="[[errorHouseholdSizeApartment]]"
>
</Redirect>

<TextAction placeholder="yymmdd-xxxx"
            mask="PersonalNumber"
            key="personalNumber"
            next="[[Continue->correctStreetAddressApartment]]"
>
  <PersonalInformationApi match="[[correctStreetAddressApartment]]"
                          nomatch="[[manualNameApartment]]"
                          error="[[manualNameApartment]]"
  >
  </PersonalInformationApi>
</TextAction>

passages.name: OfferSuccess
passages.text:
<ExternalRedirect to="Offer">
</ExternalRedirect>

passages.name: errorInfoVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  Unfortunately we can't insure houses that large right now
</Message>

<Message>
  If you want to, you can subscribe to our newsletter to be the first to know when we can insure recidences in your size!
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option>
    [[Yes, subscribe to the newsletter->NewsletterSuccess]]
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: CreateQuoteError
passages.text:
<Message>
  Uh-oh. Something technical seems to have gone wrong and we can't create and offer for you right now. We're working on it, try again soon!
</Message>

passages.name: householdSizeVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  How many people should be covered by the insurance?
</Message>

<Response>
  <when expression="householdSize > 1">
    {householdSize} people
  </when>
  <when expression="householdSize == 1">
    Just me
  </when>
</Response>

<NumberAction placeholder="2"
              key="householdSize"
              minvalue="1"
              next="[[Continue->rentOutVilla]]"
              unit="people (incl. myself)"
>
  <Tooltip>
    <Title>
      Number of insured
    </Title>
    <Description>
      E.g. partner, children or roomies that should be covered. The co-insured must live together with you to be covered by your insurance
    </Description>
  </Tooltip>
</NumberAction>

passages.name: floorsVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  How many floors does the house have? Just so you know, the cellar counts as a floor
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option>
    [[4 floors or less->householdSizeVilla]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        4 floors or less
      </Title>
      <Description>
        The house has maximum four floors, including the cellar
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option>
    [[More than 4 floors->errorFloorsVilla]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        More than 4 floors
      </Title>
      <Description>
        The house has more than four floors, including the cellar
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: StudentEligibilityCheck
passages.text:
<Redirect to="[[Offer]]"
          when="personalNumber.Age >= 30 || livingSpace > 50 || householdSize > 2"
>
</Redirect>

<Redirect to="[[StudentBrfQuestion]]"
          when="apartmentType == 'BRF'"
>
</Redirect>

<Redirect to="[[StudentRentQuestion]]"
          when="apartmentType == 'RENT'"
>
</Redirect>

<Redirect to="[[Offer]]"
          when="true"
>
</Redirect>

passages.name: extraBuildingsVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  OK, then we know. Finally, we need some information about any extra buildings on the site, if you want them to be covered by the insurance
</Message>

<Message>
  If you don't want to insure any extra buildings, just press Continue
</Message>

<GroupedResponse>
  <Title>
    Extra buildings
  </Title>
  <Each key="extraBuildings">
    {type.Label}, {area} square meters
  </Each>
</GroupedResponse>

<MultiAction maxamount="4"
             key="extraBuildings"
             next="[[Continue->emailAddressVilla]]"
>
  <Add label="Add building">
    <DropdownAction key="type"
                    label="Select type"
    >
      <Option value="GARAGE">
        Garage
      </Option>
      <Option value="ATTEFALL">
        Attefall
      </Option>
      <Option value="FRIGGEBOD">
        Friggebod
      </Option>
      <Option value="GUESTHOUSE">
        Guest house
      </Option>
      <Option value="CARPORT">
        Carport
      </Option>
      <Option value="SAUNA">
        Sauna
      </Option>
      <Option value="BOATHOUSE">
        Boathouse
      </Option>
      <Option value="OTHER">
        Other
      </Option>
    </DropdownAction>
    <NumberAction placeholder="20"
                  key="area"
                  unit="square meters"
    >
    </NumberAction>
    <SwitchAction key="hasWaterConnected"
                  label="Water connected"
                  defaultvalue="false"
    >
    </SwitchAction>
  </Add>
</MultiAction>

passages.name: apartmentTypeApartment
passages.text:
<Message>
  Do you rent or own it?
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option key="apartmentType"
          value="BRF"
  >
    [[Own it->livingSpaceApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Own it
      </Title>
      <Description>
        You own an apartment and need tenant ownership insurance
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="[apartmentType,rentalType]"
          value="[RENT,apartment]"
  >
    [[Rent it->livingSpaceApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Rent it
      </Title>
      <Description>
        You rent an apartment or own one and don't need tenant ownership insurance
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="[apartmentType,rentalType]"
          value="[RENT,apartment]"
  >
    [[Rent a sublet->livingSpaceApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Rent a sublet
      </Title>
      <Description>
        You live in an apartment that is subletted to you
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: manualNameVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  Sorry, right now we can't find your address. But no worries, we'll just ask some extra questions!
</Message>

<Message>
  What's your name?
</Message>

<TextActionSet next="[[Continue->manualAdressVilla]]">
  <TextAction title="First name"
              placeholder="Hedvig"
              key="firstName"
  >
  </TextAction>
  <TextAction title="Surname"
              placeholder="Hedvigson"
              key="lastName"
  >
  </TextAction>
</TextActionSet>

passages.name: manualInfoVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  We can't fetch any information about your house. But no worries, just fill in the information here
</Message>

<GroupedResponse>
  <Title>
    House information
  </Title>
  <Item>
    Living space: {livingSpace} sqm
  </Item>
  <Item>
    Ancillary area: {ancillaryArea} sqm
  </Item>
  <Item>
    Year of construction: {yearOfConstruction}
  </Item>
</GroupedResponse>

<NumberActionSet next="[[Fortsätt->bathsVilla]]">
  <NumberAction title="Living space"
                placeholder="120"
                key="livingSpace"
                minvalue="1"
                unit="kvadratmeter"
  >
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Living space
      </Title>
      <Description>
        Living space is the space meant to live in. Storage space, connected garage, attic and similar are not included
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </NumberAction>
  <NumberAction title="Ancillary area"
                placeholder="60"
                key="ancillaryArea"
                unit="kvadratmeter"
  >
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Ancillary area
      </Title>
      <Description>
        Examples of spaces that count as ancillary areas are storage rooms, attics and garage connected to the house
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </NumberAction>
  <NumberAction title="Year of construction"
                placeholder="1986"
                minvalue="1"
                key="yearOfConstruction"
  >
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Year of construction
      </Title>
      <Description>
        The year the house was built
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </NumberAction>
</NumberActionSet>

passages.name: rentOutVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  Are you sublettning any part of your house to someone?
</Message>

<Redirect when="householdSize > 6"
          to="[[errorhouseholdSizeVilla]]"
>
</Redirect>

<SelectAction>
  <Option key="isSubletted"
          value="false"
  >
    [[No, I don't sublet->extraBuildingsVilla]]
  </Option>
  <Option key="isSubletted"
          value="true"
  >
    [[Yes, I sublet->extraBuildingsVilla]]
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: newStreetAddressApartment
passages.text:
<Message>
  <When expression="isMover == 'true'">
    What address are you moving to?
  </When>
  <When expression="isMover == 'false'">
    No worries! What address do you want an offer for?
  </When>
</Message>

<Response>
  {streetAddress}, {postalNumber}
</Response>

<TextActionSet next="[[Continue->emailAddressApartment]]">
  <TextAction title="Address"
              placeholder="Examplestreet 21"
              large="true"
              key="streetAddress"
  >
  </TextAction>
  <TextAction title="Postal code"
              placeholder="137 50"
              mask="PostalCode"
              key="postalNumber"
  >
  </TextAction>

passages.name: StudentRentQuestion
passages.text:
<Message>
  Bonus question! Are you by any chance a student? In that case you can get our student discount!
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option key="apartmentType"
          value="STUDENT_RENT"
  >
    [[Yes->Offer]]
  </Option>
  <Option>
    [[No->Offer]]
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

  <When expression="isMover == 'true'">

passages.name: correctStreetAddressApartment
passages.text:
<Message>
  Great! Is it the residence at {streetAddress} you want to have an offer for?
</Message>

<Redirect when="isMover == 'true'"
          to="[[newStreetAddressApartment]]"
>
</Redirect>

<SelectAction>
  <Option>
    [[Yes->emailAddressApartment]]
  </Option>
  <Option>
    [[No->newStreetAddressApartment]]
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: correctStreetAdressVilla
passages.text:
<Message>
  OK! Is it the house on {streetAddress} you want an offer for?
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option>
    [[Yes->correctInfoVilla]]

passages.name: StudentBrfQuestion

passages.name: emailAddressApartment
passages.text:
<Message>
  OK! Enter you email address below to proceed to your price quote

<TextAction placeholder="your.email@here.now"
            mask="Email"
            key="email"
            next="[[Nästa->StudentEligibilityCheck]]"
>
</TextAction>

passages.name: oldInsurance
passages.text:
<Message>
  Who is your current insurer?
</Message>

<PreviousInsuranceProviderAction next="[[Continue->typeOfRecidency]]"
                                 skip="[[Okay->typeOfRecidency]]"
>
  <Tooltip>
    <Title>
      Current insurance
    </Title>
    <Description>
      Let us know who your current insurer is and we can help make the process of switching to Hedvig easier!
    </Description>
  </Tooltip>
</PreviousInsuranceProviderAction>

passages.name: typeOfRecidency
passages.text:
<Message>
  <When expression="isMover == 'false'">
    What type of residence is it?
  </When>
  <When expression="isMover == 'true'">
    What type of residence are you moving to?
  </When>
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option key="homeType"
          value="apartment"
  >
    [[Apartment->apartmentTypeApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Apartment
      </Title>
      <Description>
        For those of you who rent or own an apartment
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option>
    [[House->TypeOfHomeVilla]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        House
      </Title>
      <Description>
        For those of you who live in a detached or terraced house. We don't insure holiday homes
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="[homeType,apartmentType,rentalType]"
          value="[apartment,RENT,studentHousing]"
  >
    [[Student housing->livingSpaceApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Student housing
      </Title>
      <Description>
        For those of you who rent a student apartment or a room in a student corridor
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="[homeType,apartmentType,rentalType]"
          value="[apartment,RENT,subletter]"
  >
    [[Renting a room->livingSpaceApartment]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        Renting a room
      </Title>
      <Description>
        For those of you who rent one or several rooms in an apartment or villa
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: householdSizeApartment
passages.text:

<Redirect when="livingSpace > 250"
          to="[[errorLivingSpaceApartment]]"
>

<Response>

  <when expression="householdSize == 1">

              key="householdSize"

passages.name: livingSpaceApartment
passages.text:

  <When expression="apartmentType == 'BRF'">
    How many square meters is the apartment?
  </When>
  <When expression="rentalType == 'apartment'">
    How many square meters is the apartment?
  </When>
  <When expression="rentalType == 'villa'">
    How many square meters is the house?
  </When>
  <When expression="rentalType == 'studentHousing'">
    How many square meters is it?
  </When>
  <When expression="rentalType == 'subletter'">
    How many square meters is your room and the common areas you have access to? Common areas might include a kitchen, bathroom or living room
  </When>
</Message>

<Response>
  {livingSpace} square meters
</Response>

<NumberAction placeholder="52"
              key="livingSpace"
              minvalue="1"
              next="[[Continue->householdSizeApartment]]"
              unit="square meters"
>
  <Tooltip>
    <Title>
      Residence size
    </Title>

    </Description>

passages.name: bathsVilla
passages.text:
<Redirect to="[[errorInfoVilla]]"
          when="livingSpace >= 250 || ancillaryArea >= 250"
>

<Redirect to="[[errorAgeVilla]]"
          when="yearOfConstruction <= 1926"
>
</Redirect>

<Message>
  How many bathrooms are there in the house?

          value="2"
  >

      <Title>
        2 bathrooms

      <Description>
        There are two bathrooms with shower/bathtub in the house
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="numberOfBathrooms"
          value="99"
  >

    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        More than 2 bathrooms
      </Title>
      <Description>
        There are more than two bathrooms with shower/bathtub in the house

    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

        Year of construction
      </Title>
      <Description>
        The year the house was built
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </NumberAction>
</NumberActionSet>

passages.name: switcherStart
passages.text:
<Message>
  Hi! Let's compare Hedvig to your current home insurance
</Message>

<Message>
  Do you want an offer for your current home or are you moving?
</Message>

<SelectAction>
  <Option key="isMover"
          value="false"
  >
    [[My current home->oldInsurance]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        My current home
      </Title>
      <Description>
        It concerns a home you already have home insurance for
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
  <Option key="isMover"
          value="true"
  >
    [[I'm moving->typeOfRecidency]]
    <Tooltip>
      <Title>
        I'm moving
      </Title>
      <Description>
        It concerns a home you don't have home insurance for yet
      </Description>
    </Tooltip>
  </Option>
</SelectAction>

passages.name: Offer
passages.text:
<CreateQuoteApi uwlimits="[[ApartmentUwlimitsHit]]"
                success="[[OfferSuccess]]"
                error="[[CreateQuoteError]]"
>
</CreateQuoteApi>

<Message>
  OK! Your offer is ready!
</Message>
